response.value:
Ah yes, classic Unity gotcha! **`DontDestroyOnLoad` doesn't work on child objects** ‚Äî only root GameObjects in the hierarchy.

---

## **The Problem:**

```
Managers (parent)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ GameManager     ‚Üê DontDestroyOnLoad() called here
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ UIManager       ‚Üê DontDestroyOnLoad() called here
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ AudioManager    ‚Üê DontDestroyOnLoad() called here
```

When you call `DontDestroyOnLoad()` on a child, Unity **moves the entire parent** to the DontDestroyOnLoad scene, or it does nothing depending on the order.

---

## **Solution 1: Unparent Before DontDestroyOnLoad** ‚≠ê *Cleanest*

```csharp
// In GameManager.cs (and other managers)
void Awake()
{
    if (Instance == null)
    {
        Instance = this;

        // Unparent before making persistent
        transform.SetParent(null);
        DontDestroyOnLoad(gameObject);

        Debug.Log("[GameManager] Instance created and persisted");
    }
    else
    {
        Destroy(gameObject);
    }
}
```

**Result:** Managers automatically move to root level when scene loads, then persist.

---

## **Solution 2: Parent Object Gets DontDestroyOnLoad** ‚≠ê‚≠ê *Better organization*

Only the parent handles persistence:

```csharp
using UnityEngine;

public class ManagerContainer : MonoBehaviour
{
    public static ManagerContainer Instance { get; private set; }

    void Awake()
    {
        if (Instance == null)
        {
            Instance = this;
            DontDestroyOnLoad(gameObject);
            Debug.Log("[ManagerContainer] Managers persisted across scenes");
        }
        else
        {
            Destroy(gameObject);
            Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] Duplicate manager container destroyed");
        }
    }
}
```

**Then in child managers, remove `DontDestroyOnLoad`:**

```csharp
// In GameManager.cs
void Awake()
{
    if (Instance == null)
    {
        Instance = this;
        // NO DontDestroyOnLoad here - parent handles it
        Debug.Log("[GameManager] Instance created");
    }
    else
    {
        Destroy(gameObject);
    }
}
```

**Hierarchy:**
```
Managers (ManagerContainer.cs with DontDestroyOnLoad)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ GameManager
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ UIManager
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ AudioManager
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ RoomController
```

---

## **Solution 3: Separate Root Objects** (Traditional Unity pattern)

Keep managers as individual root objects:

```
Hierarchy:
GameManager (persists)
UIManager (persists)
AudioManager (persists)
RoomController (persists)
```

Each has its own `DontDestroyOnLoad` call.

**Pros:** Most reliable, no parent issues  
**Cons:** Less organized hierarchy

---

## **Solution 4: Hybrid - Empty Parent Just for Organization**

Create a non-persistent parent just for editor organization:

```csharp
using UnityEngine;

/// <summary>
/// Editor-only organizational helper. Gets destroyed at runtime.
/// </summary>
public class ManagerOrganizer : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Awake()
    {
        // Unparent all children, then destroy this container
        foreach (Transform child in transform)
        {
            child.SetParent(null);
            DontDestroyOnLoad(child.gameObject);
        }

        Destroy(gameObject);
        Debug.Log("[ManagerOrganizer] Managers unparented and persisted");
    }
}
```

**In Editor:** Looks organized  
**At Runtime:** Automatically separates and persists each manager

---

## üéØ **My Recommendation for Your Project:**

Use **Solution 2** (ManagerContainer) because:

‚úÖ **Clean hierarchy** in editor  
‚úÖ **Single DontDestroyOnLoad** call  
‚úÖ **Easy to debug** (one persistent parent)  
‚úÖ **Prevents duplicates** automatically  

---

## **Implementation:**

````csharp
using UnityEngine;

/// <summary>
/// Container for all persistent manager objects.
/// Only this object calls DontDestroyOnLoad.
/// </summary>
public class ManagerContainer : MonoBehaviour
{
    public static ManagerContainer Instance { get; private set; }

    [Header("Manager References")]
    public GameManager gameManager;
    public UIManager uiManager;
    public AudioManager audioManager;
    public RoomController roomController;
    public MiniGameController miniGameController;

    void Awake()
    {
        if (Instance == null)
        {
            Instance = this;
            DontDestroyOnLoad(gameObject);
            Debug.Log("[ManagerContainer] ‚úì All managers persisted across scenes");

            // Validate all managers are present
            ValidateManagers();
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] Duplicate container found - destroying");
            Destroy(gameObject);
        }
    }

    void ValidateManagers()
    {
        if (gameManager == null) Debug.LogError("[ManagerContainer] GameManager missing!");
        if (uiManager == null) Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] UIManager missing");
        if (audioManager == null) Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] AudioManager missing");
        if (roomController == null) Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] RoomController missing");
        if (miniGameController == null) Debug.LogWarning("[ManagerContainer] MiniGameController missing");
    }
}
````

**Then update GameManager.cs (and other managers):**

````csharp
