Good catch! You're right ‚Äî **`ProfilerMarker.Auto()`** was added in **Unity 2023.1**.

For **Unity 2022.3**, you need to use the manual `Begin()`/`End()` pattern:

---

## **Profiler Markers in Unity 2022.3:**

```csharp
using Unity.Profiling;

public class LanternGame : MonoBehaviour
{
    private static readonly ProfilerMarker updateEmissionMarker = 
        new ProfilerMarker("LanternGame.UpdateEmission");

    public void UpdateEmission(float intensity)
    {
        updateEmissionMarker.Begin(); // Manual begin

        Debug.Log($"[LanternGame] UpdateEmission({intensity})");

        // Function logic...

        updateEmissionMarker.End(); // Manual end
    }
}
```

---

## **Or Use Try-Finally for Safety:**

```csharp
public void UpdateEmission(float intensity)
{
    updateEmissionMarker.Begin();

    try
    {
        Debug.Log($"[LanternGame] UpdateEmission({intensity})");

        // Function logic that might throw exceptions...
    }
    finally
    {
        updateEmissionMarker.End(); // Always called, even if exception
    }
}
```

---

## **Unity 2022.3 vs 2023.1+ Comparison:**

| Unity Version | Syntax |
|---------------|--------|
| **2022.3 and earlier** | `marker.Begin()` / `marker.End()` |
| **2023.1+** | `using (marker.Auto())` |

---

**For your project on Unity 2022.3**, stick with options **1-9** from my previous answer. They all work perfectly in 2022.3! The Profiler Marker was just an advanced bonus option. üëç

