, the `t` parameter changes based on framerate, causing:
- Fast movement at start (when far away)
- **Extremely slow crawl** as it approaches target (asymptotic behavior)
- Never actually reaches the destination (mathematically approaches but doesn't arrive)

---

## **Solution 1: Use SmoothDamp** ‚≠ê *Recommended - Smoothest*

````csharp
using UnityEngine;

public class CameraController : MonoBehaviour
{
    [Header("Camera Positions")]
    public Transform roomViewPosition;
    public Transform lanternGamePosition;
    public Transform origamiGamePosition;
    public Transform calligraphyPosition;

    [Header("Movement")]
    public float smoothTime = 0.5f; // Time to reach target

    private Transform targetPosition;
    private Vector3 velocity = Vector3.zero; // Required by SmoothDamp

    public void MoveTo(Transform newTarget)
    {
        targetPosition = newTarget;
    }

    void Update()
    {
        if (targetPosition != null)
        {
            // Smooth position
            transform.position = Vector3.SmoothDamp(
                transform.position,
                targetPosition.position,
                ref velocity,
                smoothTime
            );

            // Smooth rotation
            transform.rotation = Quaternion.Slerp(
                transform.rotation,
                targetPosition.rotation,
                Time.deltaTime / smoothTime
            );
        }
    }
}
````

---

## **Solution 2: Fixed Lerp Speed** (Frame-independent)

````csharp
void Update()
{
    if (targetPosition != null)
    {
        float step = transitionSpeed * Time.deltaTime;

        transform.position = Vector3.MoveTowards(
            transform.position,
            targetPosition.position,
            step
        );

        transform.rotation = Quaternion.RotateTowards(
            transform.rotation,
            targetPosition.rotation,
            step * 50f // Degrees per second
        );
    }
}
````

---

## **Solution 3: Coroutine with Easing Curve** ‚≠ê‚≠ê *Most control*

````csharp
using System.Collections;
using UnityEngine;

public class CameraController : MonoBehaviour
{
    [Header("Camera Positions")]
    public Transform roomViewPosition;
    public Transform lanternGamePosition;
    public Transform origamiGamePosition;
    public Transform calligraphyPosition;

    [Header("Movement")]
    public float transitionDuration = 1f;
    public AnimationCurve easingCurve = AnimationCurve.EaseInOut(0, 0, 1, 1);

    private Coroutine currentTransition;

    [ContextMenu("Test Room")]
    void TestRoom() => MoveTo(roomViewPosition);

    [ContextMenu("Test Lantern")]
    void TestLantern() => MoveTo(lanternGamePosition);

    public void MoveTo(Transform newTarget)
    {
        if (currentTransition != null)
            StopCoroutine(currentTransition);

        currentTransition = StartCoroutine(TransitionTo(newTarget));
    }

    IEnumerator TransitionTo(Transform target)
    {
        Vector3 startPos = transform.position;
        Quaternion startRot = transform.rotation;

        float elapsed = 0f;

        while (elapsed < transitionDuration)
        {
            elapsed += Time.deltaTime;
            float t = elapsed / transitionDuration;
            float curveValue = easingCurve.Evaluate(t);

            transform.position = Vector3.Lerp(startPos, target.position, curveValue);
            transform.rotation = Quaternion.Slerp(startRot, target.rotation, curveValue);

            yield return null;
        }

        // Snap to final position
        transform.position = target.position;
        transform.rotation = target.rotation;
    }
}
````

---

## **Comparison:**

| Method | Smoothness | Control | Frame-Independent | Complexity |
|--------|-----------|---------|-------------------|------------|
| **Original Lerp** | ‚ùå Slow at end | Low | ‚ùå No | Simple |
| **SmoothDamp** | ‚úÖ Very smooth | Medium | ‚úÖ Yes | Simple |
| **MoveTowards** | ‚ö†Ô∏è Linear | High | ‚úÖ Yes | Simple |
| **Coroutine + Curve** | ‚úÖ‚úÖ Perfect | Very High | ‚úÖ Yes | Medium |

---

## üéØ **My Recommendation:**

For your Zen game, use **Solution 3 (Coroutine + AnimationCurve)** because:

‚úÖ **Smooth start and end** (easing)  
‚úÖ **Predictable duration** (always takes exactly `transitionDuration` seconds)  
‚úÖ **Customizable** (edit curve in Inspector for different feels)  
‚úÖ **Professional** (AAA games use this approach)  
‚úÖ **Zen aesthetic** (smooth, calming camera movements)

You can even have different curves for different transitions:
- Room ‚Üí Mini-game: Quick ease-in
- Mini-game ‚Üí Placement: Slow, contemplative
- Placement ‚Üí Completion: Graceful arc

